Josh:

We appreciate your inquiry.


DURA WOOD is 2mm of vinyl laminated to a 5mm backing for a total thickness =
of 7mm, available in rolls of 6'x30' (180 SF) and sold in full roll increme=
nts.  We do not recommend head seams.  To help avoid head seams, rolls can =
be made custom to a length of 6'x45'.


The price is $10.50 / SF, plus freight.


Freight on 2160 SF (the next full roll increment), inclusive of all fees an=
d local delivery to your warehouse location adds $1650.



The lead time is appx 5 weeks.


Seams are recommended to be welded and the welding rods cover appx 328 line=
ar feet and each spool is $225, delivered.  Note that weld is in coordinati=
ng, not matching colors so unless there is direct sunlight into the space, =
and the floor is not needing to be impervious, the weld is not always used.


If DURA WOOD will be stored prior to installation,  rolls should be stood u=
p on their ends.



Earth is tiles of 38=E2=80=9Dx38=E2=80=9D (10 SF) square-cut for glue-down =
installation and sold in full tile increments.


Based on your quantity and in 7mm thickness of color Midnight Oil the price=
 is $17.50/SF, plus freight.


Freight on 1140 SF (the next full tile increment), inclusive of all fees an=
d local delivery to your warehouse location adds $1825


The lead time is approx. 6 weeks



Notes:

  *   Pricing is valid through April 2026, after which it must be reviewed =
monthly.
  *   Adhesive is not supplied. We recommend using Dritac 7300 or Mapei Eco=
 570.
  *   Full payment is required with a purchase order via E-check, ACH, wire=
 transfer, or credit card. Credit card remittance is subject to a 3.5% proc=
essing fee.
  *   Product is manufactured and shipped on a project-by-project basis, so=
 orders are not cancellable.
  *   If tiles are stored before installation, remove all shipping bands to=
 prevent compression marks or color inconsistencies.



Earth-Tile Installation Pattern
Tiles must be installed in a brick (staggered) pattern, not corner-to-corne=
r. Rubber flooring naturally expands and contracts and is not as rigid as V=
CT or similar materials. Even with proper acclimation, subtle size variatio=
ns may occur. While these are rarely visible in individual tiles, they can =
become noticeable over large areas when installed corner-to-corner. The bri=
ck formation helps minimize visible seams and alignment issues.



Color and Shading
Shading is a natural characteristic of rubber tiles. If certain tiles appea=
r darker or lighter, position them under furniture, equipment, or along wal=
ls where cuts are typically made. Always dry-lay the tiles before gluing to=
 evaluate shading and adjust orientation as needed. Tiles have a designated=
 top and bottom=E2=80=94they may be rotated but not flipped. Use your best =
judgment to ensure a visually consistent installation. Tiles should not be =
installed if turning or flipping does not alleviate the shading issue.  In =
that event, contact us to discuss possible remedies.   Do not store or inst=
all in direct sunlight, as this can alter coloration. Note that even with U=
V Inhibitors, lighter colors are more prone to fading than are darker color=
s





We remain available should you have any further questions.



Thank you,



